snippet.textDisplay: Riverdale has become (or has been for quite some time now) a massive fanfic. The writers put everything into the show what the viewers want. If that's Archie being half naked all the time or Veronica having daddy issues. That's what the majority of the readers want because they're teenage girls. It's fan service at this point. Sure, we all know that doing everything for the fans will isn't a good idea and we see it due to Riverdale. However, it's still a widely liked show amongst teens because a good storyline isn't always their priority.

snippet.textDisplay: I also can't believe why this show is still on. It's so ridiculously dumb and painfully awful. This show even serves as bad examples in writing classes, as an example of how not to do it. I really can't believe that so many people still watch this. I can only imagine that dumb or/and really young people watch this and do like it. Season 1 was okay, not so bad but then season 2 and 3 killed it. They were so painful to watch and bad. i said to myself, if the beginning of season4 is still as bad as the other 2 seasons, i will quit this shit for good. And what can i say, it didn't got better, it got even worse so i watched only 3 or 4 episodes of season 4 and then i ended it. The writers are awful and they should take writing classes again or should quit writing completely.
